default&#xa0;
default3.
default5
default 
defaultIn 2011, over 4,000 people were killed or injured by landmines 
defaultand
default 
defaultexplosive remnants of war
default.
default 
defaultVictim assistance is an essential component of all mine action programmingdefault.  Meeting
default survivors’ needs demands a holistic approach that addresses social, economic, livelihoods, and health and rehabilitation services, access to which
default improves the quality of life of victims and their inclusion in 
defaultsociety.  
defaultWhilst DFID’s newly-published Mine Action Strategy has taken a complete view on the ‘five pillars’ of Mine Action, it has direct
defaulted
default responsibility for responding to victim assistance outside the immediate remit of its own Mine Action
default response, making
default it incumbent on DFID country programmes
default 
defaultto ensure that provision is made for victim assistance support.
default Handicap 
defaultInternational’s own experience of mine action programming across all five pillars demonstrates that a mine action programme 
defaultis only
default successful when victim assistance is fully integrated.
default&#xa0;
default3.
default6
default 
defaultHandicap International 
defaultrecommenddefaultsdefault 
defaultthat DFID
default:
default
